						<summary>

						<p>On a stone leaning against the left wall of Saṅgamēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Circa 12th century.</p>						

						<p>This is dated the Chālukya-Vikrama year, the only available details of which are Kārttīka śu. 1, Sunday.</p>						

						<p>The record refers itself to the reign of a Chālukya king whose name is lost. It seems to register some gift to a god. It is badly worn out and the other details are missing.</p>						

						</summary>
